   <text:p text:style-name="P5"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5">When broken down, some<text:span text:style-name="T7">times a</text:span> part <text:span text:style-name="T7">may </text:span>hint its pronunciation while <text:span text:style-name="T7">sometimes a </text:span>part may hint its meaning (roughly). This can be a key to memorizing kanjis.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P5"/>
   <text:h text:style-name="P8" text:outline-level="1"><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr1" draw:name="画像1" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="0.118cm" svg:y="0.739cm" svg:width="1.182cm" svg:height="1.182cm" draw:z-index="0"><draw:image draw:mime-type="image/png">
      <office:binary-data>iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAIQAAACECAYAAABRRIOnAAAACXBIWXMAAA7EAAAOxAGVKw4b
       AAABX0lEQVR4nO3UIQ7CQBRFUUrwWFxL2v2vAI9iTa0hhLuCqThHzbgnbv60zst+ga/r6AGc
       iyCI2//nsz1G7Rju/nqPnjDMtjx/bxeCEAQhCEIQhCAIQRCCIARBCIIQBCEIQhCEIAhBEIIg
       BEEIghAEIQhCEIQgCEEQgiAEQQiCEAQhCEIQhCAIQRCCIARBCIIQBCEIQhCEIAhBEIIgBEEI
       ghAEIQhCEIQgCEEQgiAEQQiCEAQhCEIQhCAIQRCCIARBCIIQBCEIQhCEIAhBEIIgBEEIghAE
       IQhCEIQgCEEQgiAEQQiCEAQhCEIQhCAIQRCCIARBCIIQBCEIQhCEIAhBEIIgBEEIghAEIQhC
       EIQgCEEQgiAEQQiCEAQhCEIQhCAIQRCCIARBCIIQBCEIQhCEIAhBEIIgBEEIghAEIQhCEIQg
       CEEQgiAEQQiCEAQhCEIQhCCIaZ2XffQIzsOFIARBHOnzBsuk4oz0AAAAAElFTkSuQmCC
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame><text:s/><text:ruby text:style-name="Ru1"><text:ruby-base><text:span text:style-name="T8">偏</text:span></text:ruby-base><text:ruby-text>へん</text:ruby-text></text:ruby><text:span text:style-name="T8"> - Left radical</text:span></text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="P9">Left radical lives on left-side in a kanji and suggests big idea of the overall meaning <text:span text:style-name="T9">of</text:span> that character.</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2">亻・<text:ruby text:style-name="Ru1"><text:ruby-base>人</text:ruby-base><text:ruby-text>にん</text:ruby-text></text:ruby><text:ruby text:style-name="Ru1"><text:ruby-base>偏</text:ruby-base><text:ruby-text>べん</text:ruby-text></text:ruby> – <text:span text:style-name="T10">Person radical</text:span></text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="P10"><text:span text:style-name="T11">T</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T12">rans</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T13">form</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T12">ed </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T11">from kanji 人 </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T14">(“person”).</text:span></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="P11">Kanji with this radical often describes a person or an action <text:span text:style-name="T15">of a person</text:span>.</text:p>
